trend_summary: Series depicts a leafy suburb gradually intensifying. Residential streets extend onto former woodland, vacant lots infill, and the northern office/industrial park doubles in roof area. Main north–south highway is widened; a new interchange appears. The small southwest airfield gains a longer runway. Tree cover shrinks modestly but golf courses and park belts persist.
notable_changes: Expansion of northern office/industrial park with several new large roofs
Widening of primary north–south highway and addition of a cloverleaf interchange
Emergence of new residential subdivisions in eastern and southern woodland patches
Extension of southwest airfield runway and enlargement of its apron
Gradual forest canopy reduction while golf courses remain largely unchanged
